entries.meaning: (zoology) A family of perciform fish native to Africa and Asia, Channidae.
examples: Through this plantation ran a creek full of snakeheads and eels, its overflow swelling the swamp around it.

entries.meaning: (slang) A Chinese smuggler, especially one who smuggles people
examples: Why would they want to run? -- To get away from the snakeheads. -- What's that? -- The snakeheads pay to get them here and then they gotta work off what they owe.

entries.meaning: (derogatory, slang, ethnic slur, US) A black person.
A showy perennial plant, Chelone glabra, found in North American marshlands; the turtlehead

A loose, bent-up end of one of the strap rails, or flat rails, formerly used on American railroads. It was sometimes so bent by the passage of a train as to slip over a wheel and pierce the bottom of a car.
